Sector 12:

Player One:

   CAPTAIN'S LOG:

   We  were  sent  out  to  investigate  pirate  activity  on  the upspin rim
of space.   It  has  been  two days without any contacts.  I have allowed the
ship's engineer  to  power down the shields in order to repair an overheating
problem in the emitter coils.

   "Captain, contacts to fore and aft."

   "How many, Ensign?"

   "Three,  four...   six.   Six  contacts  of  sizes  two  and  three.  They
are pirate vessels.  At least one may be armed with disruptors."

   Jehosaphat.   Six  ships,  one  of  them  may have disruptors, and we have
no shields.

   "Engineer, I need those shields back now!"

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Player Two:

   Hovering  in  witch  space  is  an  old tactic.  The alliance has sent out
one dreadnought  class  ship  to  catch  us.   We  will  just  wait  here for
our opportunity.

   "Commander,  their  shields  have  been  down  for  some  time now.  Shall
we attack?"

   The   alliance   vessel   lowered   their  shields  almost  6  hours  ago.
They wouldn't  do  that  in  potentially dangerous territory unless something
was wrong.

   "Make the jump into normal space.  We attack."

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Victory Conditions:

   Player   one  is  in  a  size  5  dreadnaught.   You  begin  the  scenario
with shields  powered  down.  You must destroy the pirate vessels in order to
win.

   Player  two  is  in  command  of  six  vessels.   Four of size two, two of
size three.  You must destroy the dreadnought in order to win.
@endnode

